Scores of Lowvelders crowded Blue Moon to watch Bok van Blerk perform on Saturday night, April 23. Fans young and old flocked to the front of the stage to get a chance to see Van Blerk perform up close. LEES OOK: Hier is Mpumalanga se semifinaliste vir Kwêla se Dorp van die Jaar Blue Moon opened its doors to the public at 13:00 on Saturday. Several other local artists played for the crowd before Van Blerk’s performance at 20:00. Local band Voodoo Kudu opened for Van Blerk, singing a few of their original songs as well as some well-known covers, including some songs by the well-loved band Prime Circle. The evening was filled with singing, dancing and a lot of cheering for Van Blerk and his stellar performance. Do you have more information about the story? Please send us an email to editorial@lowvelder.co.za. For free breaking and community news, visit Lowvelder’s website: Lowvelder For more news and interesting articles, like Lowvelder on Facebook, follow us on Twitter or Instagram